text: Ksenia Igorevna Bondar (born Ксения Игоревна Бондарь 1 February 1990 in Izhevsk) is a Russian volleyball player. She played at the 2008 European Under-20 Championship, 2009 World Grand Prix, and 2013 Montreux Volley Masters. She played for VK Proton Sarakov and PSK Sakhalin. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Russian volleyball players
